 ye assist her in whatsoever business she hath need of you: for she hath been a succourer of many, and of myself also.","year":60},{"id":"reclf9GEsN7DZdQ5X","ref":"Rom.16.3","text":"Greet Priscilla and Aquila my helpers in Christ Jesus:","year":60},{"id":"recFF7ewOz3AtELDt","ref":"Rom.16.4","text":"Who have for my life laid down their own necks: unto whom not only I give thanks, but also all the churches of the Gentiles.","year":60},{"id":"recJureQFmNCp5aXY","ref":"Rom.16.5","text":"Likewise greet the church that is in their house. Salute my wellbeloved Epaenetus, who is the firstfruits of Achaia unto Christ.","year":60},{"id":"rec78naxROuFDvzNZ","ref":"Rom.16.6","text":"Greet Mary, who bestowed much labour on us.","year":60},{"id":"recc2kUd1vQYSBZ7W","ref":"Rom.16.7","text":"Salute Andronicus and Junia, my kinsmen, and my fellowprisoners, who are of note among the apostles, who also were in Christ before me.","year":60},{"id":"recyDDw758uZUjtPp","ref":"Rom.16.8","text":"Greet Amplias my beloved in the Lord.","year":60}]}
